# Backend/Frontend Integration Guide тАФ Project Analytics (Mock -> Real)

## Purpose
Your frontend `AnalyticsPage` (per project) needs aggregated analytics for a selectable time range (7 / 14 / 30 days), plus a small тАЬrecent activityтАЭ feed. This document defines:
- What the backend must save (DB models / rollups)
- What backend endpoints must expose
- The response contract the frontend should consume
- Where to write integration logging for API usage and activity events

## Frontend needs (v1)
For `GET /projects/:id/analytics?rangeDays=7|14|30`, the frontend expects:
- `summary`: totals + deltas vs previous period
- `apiCallsSeries`: time series chart data (calls + errors)
- `evaluationsByEnvironmentSeries`: per-day evaluations split by environment
- `topFlags`: top flags list with enabled/on status + percent delta
- `recentActivity`: recent rule/rule-property changes (mocked for now)

## Auth
All analytics endpoints must require the same auth as other protected routes:
- Header: `Authorization: Bearer <accessToken>`

If auth fails or access token expires, the backend should return `401` so the frontend axios interceptor can refresh tokens and retry.

